Asmaa Ali al-Zarouni (born 1961) is an Emirati poet, short story writer, and educator. Her name is also transliterated as Asma' al-Zar'uni and Asma al-Zarooni.
Al-Zarouni is a native of Sharjah, and is possessed of a bachelor's degree in education. By profession she is a librarian. She has served as deputy chair of the Emirates Writers Association. She has appeared on numerous panels regarding education in her native country. Some of her work has been anthologized in English.
